03:46.184 --> 03:49.354
I'm unreal!

03:49.395 --> 03:51.564
[screams]

03:51.606 --> 03:52.774
[theme song]

03:53.775 --> 03:56.402
♪ Last night I had ♪

03:56.444 --> 03:58.863
♪ A pleasant nightmare ♪

03:58.905 --> 04:01.032
♪ Na na na na na na na ♪♪

04:02.575 --> 04:04.702
What's wrong, skank?
Why is your list blank?

04:04.744 --> 04:06.204
I thought you wanted rims.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.414
I did, but ever since
my nanny left

04:08.456 --> 04:10.291
rims don't seem
important anymore.

04:10.333 --> 04:11.584
But they are important.

04:11.626 --> 04:13.169
They make your ride
hella fresh

04:13.211 --> 04:15.046
and let all the fools
know how you roll.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.632
But they don't mean as much
to me as Carmen does.

04:17.674 --> 04:20.635
Well, maybe you could ask Santa
for a housekeeper.

04:20.677 --> 04:23.096
Or is that racial?

04:23.137 --> 04:27.058
You know what?
I don't care if it is racial.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.393
Christmas morning,
I wanna wake up

04:28.434 --> 04:29.644
and see Carmen under my tree

04:29.686 --> 04:31.354
with a big red bow on her head.

04:31.396 --> 04:33.314
Santa is a really cool person

04:33.356 --> 04:34.941
and he has a lot
of really great connections.

04:34.983 --> 04:36.609
But somehow, I just

04:36.651 --> 04:37.902
I don't think
that he's gonna be able

04:37.944 --> 04:39.153
to bring Carmen back.

04:39.195 --> 04:42.073
Then screw Santa.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.825
I'll get Carmen back on my own.

04:43.866 --> 04:45.827
I'll do like Yeezy did Keezy.

04:45.868 --> 04:48.371
I'll write a song about Carmen,
then I'll shoot a music video

04:48.413 --> 04:50.790
then I'll put it on YouTube,
then I'll hire a publicist

04:50.832 --> 04:53.418
then I'll make it go viral,
then I'll send Carmen a link

04:53.459 --> 04:55.461
then I'll make all the comments
say things like

04:55.503 --> 04:57.046
"Wow, that girl really
loves Carmen."

04:57.088 --> 04:58.506
And "Wow, Carmen
should really go back

04:58.548 --> 05:01.134
to that girl who loves her."

05:01.175 --> 05:02.844
That might actually work.

05:02.885 --> 05:04.846
[speaking in foreign language]

05:08.391 --> 05:09.600
What did he say?

05:09.642 --> 05:12.603
He said, "I love you, mommy."

05:12.645 --> 05:15.148
"I am so glad you're back
from your book tour."

05:15.189 --> 05:17.400
No, I think we should
consider a speech therapist.

05:17.442 --> 05:20.320
I'm finding it very difficult
to understand him.

05:20.361 --> 05:23.406
She can't understand him
because he's an infant.

05:23.448 --> 05:26.534
An infant
with a thick Mexican accent.

05:26.576 --> 05:27.869
(Carmen)
'Well, maybe she should
stay home'

05:27.910 --> 05:29.954
and raise him herself
in English.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.622
I beg your pardon.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.333
Have you ever written
a body of work

05:33.374 --> 05:35.251
that you were exceptionally
proud of?

05:35.293 --> 05:37.587
Darling, Carmen has a very
important job.

05:37.628 --> 05:39.839
She is caring for our baby.

05:39.881 --> 05:42.967
Why do you defend her
when she so clearly judges me?

05:43.009 --> 05:44.677
Admit it, Carmen, you judge me.

05:44.719 --> 05:50.183
I do, because you care more
about your books than your son.

05:50.224 --> 05:51.976
Carmen, don't you see?

05:52.018 --> 05:54.187
I want the baby
to love me as a mommy

05:54.228 --> 05:57.440
but I need him
to respect me as an author.

05:58.608 --> 06:01.152
