13:38.067 --> 13:40.986
- Don't take her side.
- Yes, master.

13:41.028 --> 13:43.364
'Hi. That was,
I was kidding.'

13:43.405 --> 13:46.158
I was trying to lighten
the mood..

13:46.200 --> 13:48.369
...master.

13:48.410 --> 13:50.621
And in Germany, they have
this creature called Krampus

13:50.663 --> 13:53.833
and he's like this big,
hairy monster

13:53.874 --> 13:57.586
that comes and carries away
all the bad kids in his sack.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.129
He's like Santa, except evil.

13:59.171 --> 14:02.007
And what's Krampus do
with these children he collects?

14:02.049 --> 14:03.592
I think he eats them.

14:03.634 --> 14:05.344
Seems like it would
just be easier

14:05.386 --> 14:08.222
to eat them
in the original location.

14:08.264 --> 14:10.057
Why does he have to carry them
away in a sack?

14:11.600 --> 14:13.394
I don't know.

14:13.435 --> 14:15.312
I guess it's just his thing,
you know?

14:19.692 --> 14:22.069
It's the perfect red, right?

14:22.111 --> 14:25.030
You know, every girl
needs a great red lipstick.

14:25.072 --> 14:26.782
Here. You take it.

14:26.824 --> 14:29.034
I'm not really
a red lipstick girl.

14:30.786 --> 14:32.037
Let me try.

14:33.247 --> 14:34.540
Here.

14:35.791 --> 14:37.751
[instrumental music]

14:42.006 --> 14:43.924
[sighs]

14:43.966 --> 14:45.718
Wow.

14:45.759 --> 14:48.762
Tessa, you look great.

14:48.804 --> 14:51.140
My God, you look so grown up.

14:53.225 --> 14:55.394
'Now that you're practically
an adult..'

14:55.436 --> 14:58.314
...I was kind of hoping
that maybe we could..

14:58.355 --> 15:00.441
...um..

15:00.482 --> 15:02.276
I don't know. I just..

15:02.318 --> 15:03.652
Have you ever been to Europe?

15:03.694 --> 15:07.281
I mean, are you interested
in traveling at all?

15:07.323 --> 15:09.533
- Yeah.
- Good.

15:09.575 --> 15:12.745
(Tessa)
I suppose the whole thing
was very sophisticated.

15:12.786 --> 15:15.789
I mean, there I was, wearing
the perfect red lipstick

15:15.831 --> 15:17.333
sitting in a hotel lobby
listening

15:17.374 --> 15:18.918
to stories about Berlin.

15:20.461 --> 15:22.504
But the truth is..

15:22.546 --> 15:24.506
...I had never
felt more like a kid.

15:24.548 --> 15:27.509
I wanted my house
and my tree

15:27.551 --> 15:29.637
and my Christmas stocking.

15:29.678 --> 15:31.430
And my dad.

15:31.472 --> 15:33.766
I wanted to be home
with my dad.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.105
- Look, Ryan--
- Don't call me that name.

15:41.231 --> 15:43.275
I'm not Ryan.

15:43.317 --> 15:45.152
I'm the opposite of Ryan,
which is..

15:47.404 --> 15:48.614
...Eugene.

15:49.448 --> 15:51.784
O-okay, Eugene.

15:51.825 --> 15:53.160
Look, just-just
because you're adopted

15:53.202 --> 15:54.536
doesn't make you
any less of a Shay.

15:54.578 --> 15:55.871
Don't every say
that last name again!

15:55.913 --> 15:57.164
I'm not a Shay!

15:57.206 --> 15:58.999
'I'm the opposite of a Shay'

15:59.833 --> 16:03.003
which is...Goldfarb.

16:04.213 --> 16:06.382
I'm Eugene Goldfarb!

16:06.423 --> 16:07.800
Okay. Okay.

16:07.841 --> 16:09.593
I'm Eugene Goldfarb.

16:11.136 --> 16:12.972
I'll see you in the morning.

16:14.056 --> 16:16.016
[instrumental music]

16:19.770 --> 16:21.855
Eugene can stay
as long as he likes

16:21.897 --> 16:23.607
but somebody's
gotta call his parents.

16:25.567 --> 16:27.987
♪ In my heart heart heart
heart heart ♪

16:28.028 --> 16:30.572
♪ Heart heart heart
heart heart.. ♪

16:30.614 --> 16:31.907
(Tessa)
Home for the holidays is more

16:31.949 --> 16:34.284
than just some
marketing catchphrase.

16:34.326 --> 16:36.620
For some, it's an irrepressible

16:36.662 --> 16:38.497
almost primal urge.

16:40.582 --> 16:44.128
For others, it's a reminder
of where home is.

16:44.169 --> 16:48.465
Berlin would have to wait.
I was heading home to Chatswin.

16:48.507 --> 16:52.011
And if anyone should
understand, it should be Alex.

16:52.052 --> 16:53.929
Dalia, do you like
your gloves?

16:53.971 --> 16:56.223
I got 'em from Italy.
They're made of kidskin.

16:56.265 --> 16:59.893
Thanks, mommy. These kids
must have been really cute.

16:59.935 --> 17:01.645
It's just sad,
'cause none of these boxes

17:01.687 --> 17:03.981
are big enough to be Carmen.

17:04.023 --> 17:05.315
Unless you chopped her up
and put her

17:05.357 --> 17:06.734
into separate little boxes.

17:06.775 --> 17:08.110
No, Dalia, sadly

17:08.152 --> 17:09.486
I was unable to chop up Carmen

17:09.528 --> 17:10.946
for the holidays.

17:10.988 --> 17:12.114
Dalia, there's a big present
over there

17:12.156 --> 17:13.157
you haven't opened yet.

17:13.198 --> 17:14.533
Is it rims?

17:14.575 --> 17:15.993
Uh, it looks a little big
to be rims.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.703
No, rims are really big.

17:17.745 --> 17:19.997
Oh, well-well, either way, why
don't you go ahead and open it?

17:20.039 --> 17:22.082
- It's probably just rims.
- It's not rims.

17:24.918 --> 17:26.879
[instrumental music]

17:42.811 --> 17:44.063
[both scream]

17:45.272 --> 17:47.608
I'm back, bitches!

17:47.649 --> 17:49.193
- Carmen!
- Carmen!

17:49.234 --> 17:51.820
- Aah! It's Carmen!
- Oh, my God!

17:51.862 --> 17:53.155
Oh, my God, it's Carmen!

17:53.197 --> 17:54.615
'Oh, my God!'

17:54.656 --> 17:55.783
Oh!

17:55.824 --> 17:58.285
[screams]
Oh, George.

17:58.327 --> 18:00.120
- Oh, my God!
- Watch your step.

18:00.162 --> 18:02.206
I'm gonna go play
with Carmen in my room.

18:02.247 --> 18:04.500
She'll clean this mess up
tomorrow.

18:04.541 --> 18:05.793
Come on, Carmen.

18:07.336 --> 18:09.421
It's Carmen!
You got Carmen back!

18:09.463 --> 18:13.842
You got Carmen back!
George, oh, my gosh!

18:13.884 --> 18:16.428
- Merry Christmas, Dallas.
- George.

18:16.470 --> 18:18.263
(Tessa)
It felt good to be back
in Chatswin.

18:18.305 --> 18:20.307
But before I could race
through my own front door

18:20.349 --> 18:23.060
I had to help Lisa scratch
something off her list.

18:23.102 --> 18:24.937
It's Christmas morning.
Ryan's not home.

18:24.978 --> 18:27.356
He's at Malik's and I..

18:27.397 --> 18:32.027
...I need you to talk to him
because he'll listen to you..

18:32.069 --> 18:33.195
...because he-he..

18:34.238 --> 18:35.531
[instrumental music]

18:35.572 --> 18:38.200
..he's crazy about you.

18:38.242 --> 18:40.452
He always has been.

18:40.494 --> 18:42.788
Well, uh, what do you
want me to tell him?

18:42.830 --> 18:45.207
Just tell him
that I love him.

18:45.249 --> 18:48.710
Ryan or... Malik?

18:48.752 --> 18:50.546
Alright. You know which one
I'm talking about.

18:50.587 --> 18:53.215
I'm talking about
the white one. Okay?

18:53.257 --> 18:54.967
'Okay. You know
where you're going?'

18:55.008 --> 18:57.094
Okay. Just, I just..
Thank you so much, sir.

18:57.136 --> 18:58.387
Thank you.

19:03.684 --> 19:05.227
Look, if there's anyone
who understands

19:05.269 --> 19:07.271
what you're going through,
it's me.

19:07.312 --> 19:10.440
Your biological mom
is out there.

19:10.482 --> 19:13.902
But your parents
are the people that raised you.

19:17.865 --> 19:19.783
Here.

19:19.825 --> 19:22.995
I made these business cards
on Malik's printer.

19:23.036 --> 19:24.371
(Tessa)
'Ryan, stop it.'

19:24.413 --> 19:27.457
You're not
"Eugene Goldfarb."

19:27.499 --> 19:32.754
You're Ryan Shay,
the only son of Fred and Sheila.

19:32.796 --> 19:34.214
We live across the street
from each other.

19:34.256 --> 19:35.841
You have a huge crush on me.

19:35.883 --> 19:37.968
♪ We are alone.. ♪

19:40.262 --> 19:44.308
And right now
standing on this..

19:44.349 --> 19:47.186
...picturesque
suburban street..

19:50.397 --> 19:54.735
...I'm starting to think
I may have one on you, too.

19:54.776 --> 19:57.946
♪ We might make out ♪

20:01.033 --> 20:03.827
♪ Nobody's there ♪

20:07.206 --> 20:10.209
♪ It's not that we're scared ♪

20:10.250 --> 20:12.794
♪ It's just that
it's delicate.. ♪

20:16.715 --> 20:18.008
Whoa.

20:18.050 --> 20:19.801
She used tongue!

20:20.719 --> 20:23.472
She used tongue!

20:23.513 --> 20:26.141
♪ With the words ♪

20:26.183 --> 20:30.562
♪ You've borrowed from the.. ♪♪

20:30.604 --> 20:32.648
That was the only thing
on my Christmas list.

20:32.689 --> 20:34.775
Come on.

20:34.816 --> 20:36.693
- Let's go home.
- Okay.

20:40.656 --> 20:41.907
Hey! Where are you going?

20:41.949 --> 20:43.742
You have my card!

20:43.784 --> 20:45.118
You know where to find me!

20:45.160 --> 20:46.620
(Tessa)
Ryan was still deciding

20:46.662 --> 20:48.080
where home was.

20:48.121 --> 20:50.624
But for me..

20:50.666 --> 20:52.668
...that was a question
I already answered.

20:55.837 --> 21:00.550
♪ Hold on to me as we go ♪

21:03.303 --> 21:08.558
♪ As we roll down
this unfamiliar road.. ♪

21:08.600 --> 21:10.102
Tessa. Merry Christmas.

21:10.143 --> 21:13.188
I wasn't expecting you
till the day after tomorrow.

21:13.230 --> 21:15.482
Wait. What are you doing here?

21:15.524 --> 21:17.192
Is everything okay?

21:17.234 --> 21:19.278
Yeah, dad, everything's great.

21:19.319 --> 21:21.947
♪ Just know you're not alone ♪

21:23.782 --> 21:27.577
♪ 'Cause I'm gonna make
this place your home ♪♪
